27:14.533 --> 27:17.166
Hey, you're his daughter.

27:17.233 --> 27:19.233
That's his job.

27:19.300 --> 27:21.800
I'm married, now.
He has no power over me anymore!

27:21.866 --> 27:24.233
Hey, look, I know
you two don't get along

27:24.300 --> 27:26.466
but maybe tonight
you can make a new start!

27:26.533 --> 27:27.766
I mean, you gotta
stop freakin' out

27:27.833 --> 27:29.800
every time he pushes
one of your buttons.

27:29.866 --> 27:31.833
Don't youdare
take his side, Gavin!

27:31.900 --> 27:33.933
Don't you dare!

27:52.533 --> 27:53.966
'Dad?'

27:54.033 --> 27:55.000
'Dad?'

27:56.600 --> 27:58.633
You're up to something, dad,
I heard it in your voice.

27:58.700 --> 27:59.933
I'm busy, Jessica.

28:00.000 --> 28:01.466
I wanna know what it is!

28:01.533 --> 28:03.833
You'll find out tonight.

28:03.900 --> 28:05.700
Something's wrong, isn't it?

28:05.766 --> 28:07.266
Is it medical?

28:07.333 --> 28:08.666
Nobody's dying.

28:08.733 --> 28:10.733
Don't start spending
your inheritance.

28:11.833 --> 28:13.500
Then it's something
between you and mom.

28:13.566 --> 28:14.933
Don't push it.

28:15.000 --> 28:17.266
I hate when you
keep secrets from me, dad!

28:17.333 --> 28:18.833
Just be here tonight.

28:18.900 --> 28:20.400
7:00, sharp.

28:20.466 --> 28:22.900
I hate when you threaten me
like I'm still a little child!

28:22.966 --> 28:24.933
Then grow up, Jessica.

28:26.566 --> 28:28.700
Live your own life.

28:28.766 --> 28:31.433
Stop being so damn obsessed
with your parents.

29:50.366 --> 29:52.966
Not bad for 40, huh?

29:53.033 --> 29:55.066
I don't know why
you chose me, baby

29:55.133 --> 29:57.033
'but you're gonna
have a good time.'

30:00.600 --> 30:02.533
You don't talk much, do you?

30:13.033 --> 30:15.000
Now I get it.

30:15.700 --> 30:17.866
You like to play games.

30:17.933 --> 30:20.733
Come on, baby, let's get
this shuttle in orbit.

30:24.500 --> 30:26.900
Hey, what are you doin'?

30:26.966 --> 30:28.933
Why're you getting dressed

30:34.700 --> 30:36.900
You know, I bet you're married.

30:36.966 --> 30:38.933
You saw my ring, so what?

30:43.566 --> 30:45.233
How many kids?

30:45.300 --> 30:47.300
One? Two?

30:53.033 --> 30:54.633
'Oh, you better
think again, baby.'

30:54.700 --> 30:56.666
'You don't know who
you're screwin' with.'

31:04.733 --> 31:06.033
You want money?

31:06.100 --> 31:08.766
What is this, a rip-off?

31:08.833 --> 31:10.800
Just your home number.

31:14.433 --> 31:15.700
You're dead, little girl.

31:20.933 --> 31:22.700
Excuse me, ma'am.

31:22.766 --> 31:24.633
Well, did you know
your husband's cheating on you?

31:24.700 --> 31:26.633
You are dead, bitch!

31:29.966 --> 31:32.233
You'll find him at
the Springwood Park Hotel.

31:33.666 --> 31:35.633
Bridal suite.

33:14.300 --> 33:16.900
Pop! Ha ha! Goes the weasel.

33:16.966 --> 33:18.300
Now, that's the kind
of song that'll

33:18.366 --> 33:21.600
really carve
a place in your heart, hmm.

33:32.133 --> 33:34.233
Mommy, is that you?

34:18.766 --> 34:21.100
Daddy, who's that lady?

34:21.900 --> 34:23.833
And where's mommy?

34:23.900 --> 34:25.333
'You bad girl.'

34:25.400 --> 34:27.200
'I'm getting the paddle!'

35:29.033 --> 35:31.433
'I'm not going to
spank you, Jessica.'

35:32.700 --> 35:34.933
Mommy, where are you?

35:35.000 --> 35:37.300
She's not here, now stop this!

35:39.933 --> 35:42.033
I want mommy!

35:49.266 --> 35:53.000
Come out, come out,
wherever you are.

36:12.466 --> 36:14.700
I'm scared of the paddle, daddy.

36:14.766 --> 36:17.833
I'm sorry, I'll put it away.

36:21.800 --> 36:23.833
Are you going to punish me?

36:23.900 --> 36:25.933
Not if you can keep a secret.

36:27.966 --> 36:30.333
Mommy told me never,
never to keep secrets.

36:31.133 --> 36:33.100
This is serious, Jessica.

36:35.133 --> 36:36.266
Do you know what will happen

36:36.333 --> 36:39.233
if you tell mommy
about that lady upstairs?

36:40.900 --> 36:44.133
- No.
- Something bad would happen.

36:46.566 --> 36:48.333
Worst than the boogeyman?

36:48.400 --> 36:50.033
Much worse.

36:52.300 --> 36:53.733
What is it?

36:55.066 --> 36:59.666
It's what mommies and daddies
call divorce.

36:59.733 --> 37:03.600
Divorce starts when mommy
and daddy have a big fight

37:08.666 --> 37:10.800
That sounds horrible.

37:10.866 --> 37:13.833
'Then they stop talking
to one another.'

37:17.033 --> 37:20.000
Please, don't let that happen.

37:20.066 --> 37:24.600
'Then mommy or daddy
will move to another house.'

37:28.833 --> 37:32.466
What about me?
What happens to me?

37:32.533 --> 37:35.500
If mommy and daddy
get a divorce..

37:36.566 --> 37:39.200
...we have to share you.

37:39.266 --> 37:41.200
Half and half.

38:03.600 --> 38:05.033
I had that dream.

38:05.733 --> 38:08.733
That same dream.

38:08.800 --> 38:11.333
'You know, this happens every
time you fight with your dad.'

38:13.800 --> 38:15.566
What time is it?

38:15.633 --> 38:18.100
It's time to get dressed,
or we'll be late for dinner.

38:21.600 --> 38:23.500
Maybe we shouldn't go tonight.

38:24.566 --> 38:27.200
I've got a bad feeling
about this.

38:27.266 --> 38:29.366
What your parents gonna do?
Bite you?

38:29.433 --> 38:31.000
You don't understand.

38:32.233 --> 38:34.533
You know, you're right,
I'll never understand.

38:34.600 --> 38:37.333
Why do you let them
drive you crazy?

38:37.400 --> 38:39.866
You act like
you're responsible for them.

38:39.933 --> 38:42.000
Dad sneezes, you get a cold.

38:42.066 --> 38:43.900
Mom gets a headache,
you take the blame.

38:43.966 --> 38:45.100
It's nuts.

38:45.166 --> 38:47.200
Gavin, please back off a bit.

38:48.933 --> 38:50.900
I need your help tonight.

38:53.533 --> 38:54.833
I'm sorry.

38:58.400 --> 38:59.933
You know, truth is, uh

39:00.000 --> 39:02.933
we probably are in
for a very boring evening.

39:06.933 --> 39:08.600
We've made your favorite
tonight, Jessy.

39:08.666 --> 39:09.766
Roast beef, rare.

39:09.833 --> 39:11.600
Hmm, I can taste
the blood already.

39:11.666 --> 39:14.133
Your father's just putting
on the finishing touches.

39:14.200 --> 39:15.633
They're here, dear.

39:17.566 --> 39:19.166
It's about time.

40:01.266 --> 40:03.300
'I'm so full I could die.'

40:05.033 --> 40:07.933
'I'll be glad
to carve you some more.'

40:08.000 --> 40:11.333
'Jessica, do you want your
father to carve you so more?'

40:14.333 --> 40:16.200
I-I guess I'm not hungry.

40:19.566 --> 40:22.000
Um, how about dessert?

40:25.066 --> 40:27.033
I think we should
tell them now, Marianne.

40:30.133 --> 40:32.933
We decided to wait
till after your honeymoon.

40:34.400 --> 40:36.200
...to make this announcement.

40:36.266 --> 40:39.533
Jessie, we didn't wanna
spoil it for you.

40:43.266 --> 40:45.433
Your mother and I
are getting divorced.

40:48.833 --> 40:50.700
'I know there's a
certain irony to this--'

40:50.766 --> 40:53.933
You can't,
I won't let you.

40:54.000 --> 40:56.533
'Jessie, I know
this is hard for you'

40:56.600 --> 40:58.533
'but it's hard for us too.'

40:59.800 --> 41:02.633
I kept my promise, dad.

41:02.700 --> 41:04.533
I didn't say a word.

41:05.533 --> 41:07.100
You have no right to do this!

41:07.166 --> 41:08.900
What are you talking about?

41:08.966 --> 41:10.933
You know damn well
what I'm talking about!

41:13.466 --> 41:17.233
I-I spent my whole life
keeping you two together.

41:21.166 --> 41:23.200
You're not going
to do this to me.

41:25.700 --> 41:27.366
Take it back.

41:27.433 --> 41:28.400
'Jess, what's wrong with you?'

41:28.466 --> 41:30.200
'They're trying to make it easy
for you.'

41:30.266 --> 41:32.866
- Take it back.
- 'Jessie, please.'

41:32.933 --> 41:35.933
Take it back or I'll tell,
I'll tell, I'll tell..

41:36.000 --> 41:37.533
Jess, come on, let's go home.

41:37.600 --> 41:39.433
Jessie, please.

41:39.500 --> 41:44.200
I never told mom
about that lady, dad.

41:45.600 --> 41:50.300
I never told her about
any of your la-la-ladies.

41:51.800 --> 41:54.500
I kept my promise.

41:54.566 --> 41:56.866
Gavin, get her out of here!

41:56.933 --> 41:59.200
Mommy, he made me swear.

41:59.266 --> 42:02.433
Jessie, I knew about
the other women.

42:07.600 --> 42:11.000
- You knew?
- I've always known.

42:31.900 --> 42:34.200
Kill me, kill me!

42:36.133 --> 42:38.200
Your place or mine, baby?

42:45.133 --> 42:47.100
I'm sorry for what I did.

42:48.666 --> 42:50.866
It was a mistake.

42:50.933 --> 42:53.633
I was crazy,
I was mad at my father.

42:53.700 --> 42:57.733
Yeah, I heard your parents
are getting a divorce.

42:57.800 --> 42:59.700
They sure suckered at you,
didn't they?

43:06.533 --> 43:11.000
All those years, it killed you
keeping that secret, didn't it?

43:14.400 --> 43:15.733
Poor little girl.

43:17.800 --> 43:19.700
I'm so scared.

43:20.700 --> 43:22.600
You were always scared.

43:22.666 --> 43:25.200
Guess you saw yourself as
the guardian of their marriage.

43:26.166 --> 43:27.700
Big mistake.

43:33.666 --> 43:35.600
What are you going to do?

43:37.366 --> 43:39.400
Hey, your folks
are getting a divorce.

43:42.100 --> 43:45.400
Just like you always do.

43:45.466 --> 43:47.633
'A thing like that
can really cut a girl.'

43:57.133 --> 43:58.066
No!

44:04.766 --> 44:07.400
'I know, doctor, I just wanted
to see her for a second.'

44:11.866 --> 44:13.333
I can't stand it.

44:13.400 --> 44:15.633
'It happens every time
she looks at me.'

44:17.433 --> 44:19.433
Jess, please..

44:19.500 --> 44:20.600
Jessie, please.

44:23.533 --> 44:26.800
No. Get away! Get away!

44:29.900 --> 44:31.533
Get away!

44:35.766 --> 44:38.366
The ties that bind.

44:38.433 --> 44:39.666
Ha ha ha.

44:39.733 --> 44:42.633
The chains of love..

44:42.700 --> 44:46.500
...unbreakable, indestructible.

44:49.200 --> 44:51.533
And tasty too.
